<subSubSection id="66B0A1F4FF81FFBB38E0A464FCB9FD8B" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2E15F27FFF81FFBB38E0A464FE54FE6F" blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1507]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis id="1CDE2E6DFF81FFBB38E0A464FEECFE1B" bold="true" box="[199,314,366,391]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Species with bluish reflection of mesonotum and green reflection of abdomen (
<figureCitation id="B691EEFAFF81FFBB3CE4A464FAC0FE1B" box="[1219,1302,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,225,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,195,1942]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Merodon rufipes, male: a—dorsal view (scale 1 mm); b—thorax, dorsal view (scale 1 mm); c—head, lateral view (scale 0.5 mm); d—head, anterior view (scale 0.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/556022/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
a); posterior half of mesonotum covered with black pile; tergites completely covered in pale pile in male. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E9AA89FCFF81FFBB3D5AA499FEDFFE52" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adriaticus">
<emphasis id="1CDE2E6DFF81FFBB3D5AA499FEDFFE52" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">M. adriaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the presence of mostly pale pile on eyes and completely pale pilosity on scutellum (
<figureCitation id="B691EEFAFF81FFBB3934A4D0FEB3FE6F" box="[275,357,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,225,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,195,1942]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Merodon rufipes, male: a—dorsal view (scale 1 mm); b—thorax, dorsal view (scale 1 mm); c—head, lateral view (scale 0.5 mm); d—head, anterior view (scale 0.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/556022/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E15F27FFF81FFBB38E0A4F4FCB9FD8B" blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1507]" box="[199,879,510,535]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
